<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="404" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.428/587</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The British Appointed Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Geddes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-20"><hi rend="italic">April 20,
                                        1920</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 250</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honour to refer to Mr.
                                Long’s note of March 24th communicating a proposed amendment to
                                Article 2 of the Sockeye Salmon Treaty and to inform you that the
                                Government of the Dominion of Canada are prepared to accept this
                                amendment.</p>
                            <p>At the same time I am requested by the Canadian Government to urge
                                that as early a date as possible may now be definitely fixed for the
                                signature of the Treaty as amended.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">A. C. Geddes</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>